Jana Kramer and Mike Caussin’s kids Jolie, 3, and Jace, 12 months, had a “successful” Santa visit, the “Beautiful Lies” singer, 36, wrote on Instagram on December 15. “Jolie asked for a unicorn… no surprise there,” the actress captioned the festive family photo. “As a mom I feel like I now understand when my parents said they don’t want anything and just want to see their kids happy and healthy.

item.title: Gilma Avalos Age: NBC 4, Net Worth, Wedding, Bio, Wikipedia, Pregnancy, Spouse, Family, and Salary
item.description: Gilma Avalos Biography and Wikipedia Gilma Avalos is a celebrated American journalist. Currently, she works at NBC 4 New York / WNBC as an anchor and reporter alongside fellow anchor Adam Kuperstein from 6 PM and 11 PM newscasts on Saturday and Sunday. Previously, before joining WNBC, she worked as an anchor at CBS 11 / KTVT anchoring weekday afternoon newscasts and delivered breaking news coverage for five years.

item.title: Kevin Hart Started Beef To Sell Movie Tickets
item.description: Katt Williams isn’t backing down from Kevin Hart. The comedian’s views of Tiffany Haddish have spilled over into harsh critiques about Hart, with Williams accusing him of crafting their beef for sales. On Friday (Sept. 28), Williams hopped on Instagram Live to call out Hart and clear up comments about his tour style. “Kevin’s been pretending he’s on a world tour but that ni**a been everywhere but f**king here,” he said.

item.title: Mom Jeans That Might Even Have You Ditching Your Skinny Jeans
item.description: Us Weekly has affiliate partnerships. We receive compensation when you click on a link and make a purchase. Learn more! Us Weekly has affiliate partnerships so we may receive compensation for some links to products and services. There are always a ton of denim debates going on in the fashion world. Blue or black? Ripped or clean? Cuffed or cropped? And, of course, skinny or not? Do we stick with our beloved, trusted skinny jeans, or do we dip into a style like a mom jean instead?

item.title: Paris Hilton Explains the Origin of Thats Hot Catchphrase
item.description: Hot or not? Paris Hilton revealed where she got her famous catchphrase, “That’s hot,” nearly two decades after its creation. She began using the phrase in the early 2000s and its origin is pretty close to home. “The 2000s were all about Britney Spears, boy bands. It was all about monograms and labels, like Chanel and Dior and Louis Vuitton,” Hilton, 38, told Vogue in an interview on Wednesday, December 18, when talking about the fashions of the early ‘00s.

item.title: Rick Moranis Revealed That He May Be Hollywood's Nicest Guy After His Wife Died
item.description: Quick LinksWhy Rick Moranis Sacrificed His Hollywood Career More Proof That Rick Moranis Is A Really Nice Guy From 1976 until 1984, SCTV was one of the edgiest and funniest shows on television. A Canadian sketch comedy show that has often been compared to Saturday Night Live, just like its American counterpart, SCTV starred many people who went on to become comedy legends. For example, SCTV starred John Candy, Martin Short, Catherine O’Hara, Eugene Levy, and Rick Moranis.

item.title: The Truth About Mary And Romain's Relationship
item.description: Although he wasn't part of the real estate team at the time, Romain Bonnet has been a staple on 'Selling Sunset' since the first episode. Of course, from the beginning, some fans couldn't stand Romain Bonnet. Fans questioned whether his accent was real, whether the relationship between him and Mary was legit, and wondered about the pair's age gap (Romain is 12 years younger than his lady). It turns out, the French transplant is both a model and a former chef (pastries, specifically), so that much is true that's been hinted at on the show.

item.title: Who Is Dr Jennifer Jen Ashton Fiance? ABC News Correspondent Reportedly Engaged To Boyfriend T
item.description: Doctor Jennifer Jen Ashton is reportedly known for being in a relationship with boyfriend Todd Ellerin after her divorce and the death of her ex-husband. Learn about her relationship and net worth in this piece. Jennifer Lee Garfien Ashton, popularly known as Jennifer “Jen” Ashton, is a physician, author, and television correspondent who was born on April 23, 1969. Moreover, she is the chief health and medical editor for ABC News and Good Morning America, as well as the lead women’s health correspondent for The Dr.

item.title: Who Is Jim English Wife? The Tower Actors Family Life Explored
item.description: An actor cast in ‘The Tower’ ITV, Jim English aged 43, has not shared much about his wife or personal details. Here is everything about him, learn it. Jimmy Olatokunbo Akingbola aka Jim English is a British actor who works in television, theatre, and film. In 1996, he gained education in acting and earned a 3-year diploma course from the Academy of Live and Recorded Arts (ALRA) located in Wandsworth, London.

item.title: '90 Day Fianc': 10 Couples Who Are Now Parents
item.description: As entertaining as 90 Day Fiance is, it's important to remember that the stars on the hit TLC show are real people. Critics have accused the show of being fake and staged. Granted, some 90 Day Fiancé moments were too ridiculous to ever be real, but there are also some very real moments on the show. Whatever the case may be, there's no denying that 90 Day Fiancé is a binge-able show and a guilty pleasure for most.

item.title: 5 chilling details about Michelle Mockbees murder
item.description: On February 18, 2023, 15-year-old Lydia Elking of Lake Holy person Louis, Missouri, was killed during a messed up burglary in which two outfitted teens started shooting at the vehicle she was going in. A GoFundMe pledge drive crusade has been set up by Dani Elking, which makes reference to that the gifts will be utilized for burial service costs, and the other assets will assist with the mourning system.

item.title: Bill Block Buys Sunset Strip Compound With Jetliner Views Estate For $6.6 Million
item.description: American film producer who has been CEO of Miramax since April 2017. His producing credits include W., District 9, Fury, Bad Moms, Dirty Grandpa, Halloween, and Halloween Kills Bill Block has found a new place to hang his hat, having picked up a Spanish-style gem in the steep hills directly above L.A.’s bustling Sunset Strip. On and off the market since earlier this year, once for as much as $9 million, the home’s listing price was reduced twice before going to the Miramax CEO at a substantial $2.

item.title: Lori Loughlin's L.A. Home for Sale After College Admissions Scandal
item.description: Lori Loughlin and husband Mossimo Giannulli have put their Los Angeles home on the market for $17.5 million, Us Weekly can confirm. The couple’s sprawling 11,800-square-foot house, which was built in 2019, is located in the exclusive gated Hidden Hills community within Calabasas, California. The mansion provides panoramic views overlooking the mountain vistas and boasts six bedrooms and seven full bathrooms. Some amenities within the property include a swimming pool, bocci ball court, home theater and wine cellar.

item.title: Kim Zolciak and Kroy Biermann's Fighting Started Last Week, Argued Fi

item.title: Does Chelsea Handler Still Talk To Her Ex-Boyfriend 50 Cent?

The two dated for a couple of months in 2010 but later decided to call things off as Handler admitted that R&B singer Ciara was allegedly still pursuing after him and it had made her feel somewhat uncomfortable.

item.title: Who Owns BMW? BMW Company History
item.description: Have you ever wondered who owns BMW, the iconic luxury automobile brand? In this article, we delve into the rich history of BMW, its origins, and its journey to becoming one of the world’s leading automotive companies. From its humble beginnings as Bayerische Flugzeug-Werke AG (BFW) to its prominence today as a premium supplier of automobiles, motorcycles, and mobility services, BMW has a fascinating story to tell. Established in 1916, BMW has evolved over the years, embodying innovation, luxury, and performance in every vehicle it produces.

item.description: Brock Lesnar has taken the UFC by storm and his post-fight antics Saturday night after beating Frank Mir for the Undisputed Heavyweight Championship was an example of classic wrestling booking 101.  After the final bell had sounded with Lesnar beating Mir to the point of his face looking like a halloween mask that had accidentally been washed, Brock Lesnar continued to taunt Mir by getting in his face, the fans by flipping them the double bird, and UFC’s corporate sponsor, Bud Light, by claiming he was going to drink Coors Light instead.

But the truth is now — as I get older — I got a little more experience. I got a little more clarity,” Clark, 40, said via an Instagram video shared on Wednesday, January 17.

item.title: Dua Lipa Stuns In $10 Million 100-Carat Diamond Necklace At MET Gala
item.description: Dua Lipa stole the show at the 2023 MET Gala with her stunning (and very expensive) vintage look. The singer showed up in a stunning Chanel wedding dress from the fashion house’s 1992 collection. The ball gown featured white tweed with a Basque waist and black trim. The dress was originally worn by Claudia Schiffer when it debuted on the runway. RELATED: Adidas Sued By Investors For Ignoring Concerns Over Kanye West’s Behavior

item.title: Elizabeth Sulcer x Marc Fisher Boot Collection: Editor's Picks
item.description: Elizabeth Sulcer is the stylist to the stars. Her clients include Gigi and Bella Hadid, Kim Kardashian, Adrianna Lima — and the list goes on! To aid in your quest to slay the street style game, the fashion expert just teamed up with Marc Fisher LTD to launch the brand’s first-ever design collaboration. “Excited to launch my first footwear collection,” Sulcer wrote in an Instagram caption on Wednesday, November 5, to celebrate the big news.

item.title: Indonesia Earthquake Sends Locals In Fear; Tsunami Alert Issued
item.description: Everyone pray for our brothers & sisters in Indonesia. It’s being reported that a massive earthquake off Indonesia’s western coast triggered tsunami fears across the Indian Ocean today, sending residents in coastal cities fleeing to high ground in cars and on the backs of motorcycles. As Yahoo! states via The Assiciated Press, a strong aftershock nearly three hours after the initial earthquake sparked a new wave of panic, with the local government issuing a fresh tsunami warning.

item.title: JoAnna Garcia Swisher Shares Her Best Dinnertime Tips and Tricks
item.description: As a working mom of two, JoAnna Garcia Swisher knows how to throw together dinner in a pinch. The Sweet Magnolias star, 44, shared her best tips and tricks for making dinnertime less of a chore exclusively with Us Weekly — and the first step requires planning out meals in advance. For Garcia Swisher, coming up with a weekly dinner menu “makes shopping and prepping easy.” She also takes recipe requests from her husband, Nick Swisher, and their daughters Emerson, 10, and Sailor, 7, “so everyone is excited about dinnertime.

item.description: Memories remain. item.description: Master P is apparently weary from his reputation being slandered by former associates, as he’s proposed a law that would prevent disgruntled artists from mentioning his name moving forward. The 52-year-old’s declaration comes amid a back-and-forth with rapper Fat Trel following previous comments the Washington D.C. artist made about his dealings with the rap mogul. item.title: Is Harry Belafontes Still Alive? When Did He Start Working for Change?
item.description: Harry Belafonte is a famous singer, songwriter, activist, and actor who was born in Jamaica. Harry Belafonte was born to Harold George Bellanfanti, Sr., and Melvine Love Bellanfanti on March 1, 1927, at Lying-in Hospital in Harlem, New York, United States. The parents of Harry Belafonte were both born in Jamaica. Both Melvine and Harold’s parents worked; Melvine was a maid and Harold was a cook. He started out at Wolmer’s Schools and ended up at George Washington High School.

item.title: Jionni LaValle: 5 Things You Dont Know About Snooki's Fiance

He’s a real Jersey Boy.

item.title: Lewis Hamilton Has One Of The Most Expensive Real Estate Portfolios
item.description: Quick LinksThe Luxurious Home in Kensington The Glamorous Geneva Apartment The Princely Monaco Condo The Expensive Big Apple Penthouse Lewis Hamilton, undeniably one of the most successful drivers in Formula One, has reached an insane level of fame, earned a corresponding amount of money, and is living the high life. The world-class racer is an unparalleled property dealer of the top-notch level. Over the years, the seven-time F1 champ has accumulated a portfolio of opulent abodes spanning across the world’s fanciest capitals.

item.title: The Fiend Defeats Daniel Bryan In Brutal Strap Match, Retains Universal Championship
item.description: At WWE Royal Rumble,”The Fiend” Bray Wyatt defended the WWE Universal Championship against Daniel Bryan in a Strap Match. The two stars have been locked in a heated, violent feud for several weeks. Bryan took the fight to The Fiend early on but a powerbomb floored the challenger. The Fiend whipped Bryan with the strap. Bryan tried diving onto The Fiend, who caught him and threw him into the barricade. The Fiend continued to repeatedly whip Bryan with the strap.

item.description: Team USA phenomenon Simone Biles is basking in her success after taking gold at the 2016 Olympic Games. With the most gold medals in world gymnastics championship history checked off her list of accomplishments, the trailblazing gymnast’s success is anything but accidental. The Biles, on the other hand, was largely unplanned. Biles’ signature move, which she dubs a “double lay half out,” entered the International Federation of Gymnastics’ Code of Points in 2013 when she became the first gymnast to complete the motion in a world competition.

item.title: NYC Thief Steals Over $800 Worth Of Toothpaste From Duane Reade
item.description: This sounds like a possible episode of My Strange Addiction. According to DNA Info, a thief is still at large after stealing over $800 worth of toothpaste from a New York City-based Duane Reade. Located in the Columbus Circle section of Manhattan, the unidentified assailant entered the store around 11:30 a.m. earlier this month and stacked his basket with an estimate of 135 boxes of toothpaste. Given that there was no security personnel present, the thief managed to get away with the items.

item.title: Quentin Tarantino Stands Firm On Retirement After Next Film
item.description: The inevitable day seems like it's finally come. The ever so prolific film director Quentin Tarantino recently announced that he'll be putting his masterful mind for making cinema hits into retirement after his next project. "I know film history and from here on in, filmmakers do not get better," the director told Bill Maher during his guest appearance on the HOB's Real Time. Though Maher was persistent in coxing Tarantino off the retirement ledge, the director was persistent in his stance on throwing in the towel.

item.title: This Is Why Fans Are Calling Tina Fey 'Self-Righteous' And Judgy
item.description: She's been in the industry a long time, and Tina Fey clearly knows what it takes to be successful, whether in comedy or any other corner of Hollywood. She's more than just a comedian and actress, and she's done just about every job in the industry. Yet some people are beginning to wonder whether Fey is really something special, or if she's been playing off a not-so-great personality with humor for way too long.

item.title: What Happened To The Actor Who Played Finn From The 100
item.description: In the beginning, The 100 was essentially underdog. Sure, The CW series offers an interesting premise that takes place in post-apocalyptic Earth (the storytelling was rough at first, but the show eventually found its rhythm). However, the cast was full of relatively new actors (with the exception of Isaiah Washington who starred in the series around the time that he just exited Grey’s Anatomy). RELATED: The Most Overrated CW Shows (And 5 Actually Good) Among the show’s regular cast members was Thomas McDonell, the man who portrayed Finn Collins across 22 episodes.

item.title: Who Are The Birth Parents Of Tom Cruise And Nicole Kidmans Adopted Kids?
item.description: During their decade-long marriage, Tom Cruise and Nicole Kidman adopted two children – Isabella (born in 1992) and Connor (born in 1997). As with all aspects of their relationship, Tom and Nicole’s adoption news was highly publicized. There was speculation over why they chose to adopt, how they connected with their kids, and who Isabella and Connor’s biological families were. Here’s everything we know. Tom And Nicole Had Fertility Issues, But Had Biological Kids With Other People During their marriage, Tom and Nicole had a challenging journey to become parents.
